7. Conclusion
Implemented a 6LoWPAN node using an embedded linux platform and a low power 802.15.4 radio. The main advantages of using IPv6 in sensor node networks was that it enables the use of standard networking tools, which were originally developed for the Internet, also for WSNs. Furthermore, it simplifies the task of interlinking WSNs
over the Internet, as there was no need for an advanced gateway. The packets can simply be forwarded on the link-
layer. IPv6 is important for the long-term development of the Internet, but a switch to IPv6 is almost impossible as long as most services are not offered over IPv6.
